COORDINATION SERVICES AGREEMENT THIS COORDINATION SERVICES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), is entered into as of March 26, 2012, by and between High Majestic Interconnection Services, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“High Majestic Interconnection”), and High Majestic Wind Energy Center, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“High Majestic I”, together with High Majestic Interconnection, the “Parties” and each a “Party”). RECITALS WHEREAS, High Majestic I owns and operates a wind energy generation facility with a nameplate capacity of 79.5 MW (the “High Majestic I Project”); WHEREAS, High Majestic I’s affiliate, High Majestic Wind II, LLC (“High Majestic II”) is developing and intends to construct, own and operate a wind energy generation facility with a nameplate capacity of approximately 80 MW (the “High Majestic II Project”, and jointly with High Majestic I, the “Projects”, and each of them individually, a “Project”); WHEREAS, High Majestic I is a party to a certain Large Generator Interconnection Agreement by and among itself, Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (“SPP”) and Southwestern Public Service Company (d/b/a Xcel Energy) (“Xcel”), dated as of October 31, 2005 (as amended, the “LGIA”) which provides for Interconnection Services (as defined in the LGIA) for a Generating Facility (as defined in the LGIA) to be constructed in two phases, correlating to the High Majestic I Project and High Majestic II Project, with an aggregate capacity not to exceed 160 MW, and concurrently with the execution of this Agreement, High Majestic I and High Majestic Interconnection will enter into an Assignment and Assumption Agreement, dated as of the date hereof (the “Assignment and Assumption Agreement”), pursuant to which the LGIA will be assigned to High Majestic Interconnection under the terms and conditions specified therein in order to enable High Majestic Interconnection to provide the interconnection services hereunder; WHEREAS, High Majestic I is a party to an Operations and Maintenance Agreement dated as of December 16, 2009 between High Majestic I and NextEra Energy Operating Services, LLC (such agreement, or such other agreement executed in the future by High Majestic I and a successor entity to NextEra Energy Operating Services, LLC, the “Common Facilities O&M Agreement”), with respect to the operation and maintenance of the Common Facilities; WHEREAS, High Majestic I, High Majestic II and High Majestic Interconnection are entering into a Common Facilities Agreement, dated as of the date hereof, to allow High Majestic II and High Majestic Interconnection to use certain real property interests, personal property, fixtures, equipment and/or facilities owned by High Majestic I (the “Common Facilities Agreement”); and WHEREAS, High Majestic I and High Majestic Interconnection are entering into this Agreement to establish the terms and conditions by which High Majestic Interconnection enables High Majestic I to receive the service from High Majestic Interconnection that it requires to deliver its energy to the Point of Interconnection (as defined in the LGIA) under the LGIA and it is contemplated that High Majestic II and High Majestic Interconnection will enter into a coordination services agreement on terms that are substantially similar to this Agreement and are no more favorable to High Majestic II than the terms in this Agreement are to High Majestic I (the “HMII Coordination Services Agreement”, and together with the LGIA, the Common Facilities Agreement and this Agreement, the “HMI and HMII Agreements”) to establish the terms and conditions by which High Majestic Interconnection will enable High Majestic II to receive the service from High Majestic Interconnection that it requires to deliver its energy to the Point of Interconnection (as defined in the LGIA) under the LGIA;
NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows: AGREEMENT TERM; EARLY TERMINATION Term: The term of this Agreement shall commence on the date first written above and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, (b) pursuant to Section 1.2 of this Agreement, or (c) pursuant to Section 6.1 of this Agreement. Early Termination: This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by either Party and without further liability of any Party to any other Party, upon the earlier date that (a) High Majestic I, or its successor and assignee, shall have permanently ceased operation of the High Majestic I Project for the production of electric energy or (b) High Majestic Interconnection assigns, transfer and conveys its rights and obligations under the LGIA to High Majestic I in accordance with the final sentence of Section 1 of the Assignment and Assumption Agreement. SERVICES Nature of Services: High Majestic Interconnection shall provide the services hereunder to High Majestic I as needed to enable all of the energy from the High Majestic I Project to reach the transmission system of Xcel in accordance with the LGIA (the “Coordination Service”). The Coordination Service provided by High Majestic Interconnection to High Majestic I shall not relieve High Majestic Interconnection of its obligations under the LGIA. The Parties also acknowledge that High Majestic Interconnection expects to enter into a corresponding Coordination Service Agreement with High Majestic II, including terms and conditions substantially equivalent to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement. Obligations of High Majestic Interconnection: High Majestic Interconnection (pursuant to its rights under the Common Facilities Agreement), through the Operator pursuant to the Common Facilities O&M Agreement (as defined in the Common Facilities Agreement), shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is consistent with its obligations under the LGIA and which enables the energy from High Majestic I to reach the transmission system of Xcel. To the extent necessary in order to exercise the rights and perform such obligations, High Majestic Interconnection hereby delegates its rights and obligations hereunder to High Majestic I, which shall carry out (and shall direct the Operator, as appropriate, to carry out) such rights and obligations to the extent necessary through the Common Facilities O&M Agreement. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, High Majestic Interconnection (pursuant to its rights under the Common Facilities Agreement), through the Operator pursuant to the Common Facilities O&M Agreement (as defined in the Common Facilities Agreement) agrees to: Perform its obligations under this Agreement and the LGIA in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the LGIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the LGIA; Comply with all provisions of the LGIA to which it is subject (and all insurance requirements, payments due, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof); Promptly provide to High Majestic I any notices it receives under the LGIA from SPP or Xcel, including any notices regarding emergencies under Article 13 of the LGIA; Not take any steps, or omit to take any steps, without High Majestic I’s written consent, to amend, assign or terminate the LGIA; Perform necessary maintenance on the Common Facilities as defined and agreed to in the Common Facilities Agreement; and Ensure that, to the maximum extent possible, any actions taken, or omitted to be taken, by High Majestic II that may or do cause High Majestic Interconnection to fail to comply with the LGIA, do not affect the Coordination Service received by High Majestic I hereunder. Obligations of High Majestic I: High Majestic I shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and facilitates High Majestic Interconnection’s performance under and compliance with the LGIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, High Majestic I agrees to: Operate the High Majestic I Project in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the LGIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the LGIA; Facilitate High Majestic Interconnection’s compliance with all provisions of the LGIA to which High Majestic Interconnection is subject (and all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as it relates to the High Majestic I Project; Not take any action (nor refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the LGIA by High Majestic Interconnection; Use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of its Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default under the LGIA, and if such default occurs, to promptly assist High Majestic Interconnection to cure such default in accordance with the terms of the LGIA; Comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by High Majestic Interconnection, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the LGIA with respect to the High Majestic I Project; Provide High Majestic Interconnection with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of the High Majestic I Project required for High Majestic Interconnection to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the LGIA; and Provide to High Majestic Interconnection copies of all notices and instructions received by it that affect High Majestic Interconnection’s performance under the LGIA. Prior Written Consent: Except as set forth in this Agreement, neither Party shall take any action that results in the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights or increases the obligations or responsibilities of the other Party under this Agreement, without the prior written consent of the other Party. No Joint and Several Liability with High Majestic II: The Parties acknowledge that this Agreement does not subject High Majestic I to joint and several liability for any actions taken by High Majestic II that may cause non-compliance by High Majestic Interconnection with the LGIA. COST REIMBURSEMENT Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses: Under the LGIA, High Majestic Interconnection is responsible for certain expenses, including potential costs under Section 10.5 of the LGIA for operations and maintenance expenses. Such expenses, and those expenses incurred to administer Coordination Services to High Majestic I and High Majestic II which are not directly caused by either High Majestic I or High Majestic II, shall be paid for as provided in Section 9 of the Common Facilities Agreement, CHANGE IN LAW Change in Law: In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Coordination Service or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement. CERTAIN COVENANTS Authority and Operational Abilities: Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement. Adverse Events: If an operational issue arises at the High Majestic I Project or High Majestic II Project that is reasonably expected to result in a breach by High Majestic Interconnection of the LGIA or this Agreement (an “Adverse Event”), High Majestic Interconnection shall promptly take all commercially reasonable action to resolve such issue, including curtailing the Project that is causing the Adverse Event. In the event of such curtailment, energy deliveries to the to the Point of Interconnection (as defined in the LGIA) from the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall be limited as necessary until the Adverse Event has been cured in the reasonable judgment of High Majestic Interconnection and High Majestic I. If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event caused by the High Majestic I Project or the High Majestic II Project, High Majestic Interconnection incurs costs, expenses, or penalties of any kind, the Project that has caused such Adverse Event shall be solely responsible for reimbursing High Majestic Interconnection for any such costs, expenses or penalties. In the event that both Projects are responsible for the Adverse Event, and to the extent that High Majestic Interconnection, in its reasonable discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Adverse Event between the Projects, each Project shall be responsible for its allocable portion of the applicable costs, expenses or penalties. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for High Majestic Interconnection, as determined in its reasonable discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, each Project will be liable for its Pro Rata Share (as defined in the Common Facilities Agreement) of such costs, expenses or penalties. Priority of Curtailment: Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, in the event of curtailment pursuant to the LGIA (or pursuant to applicable operating guides or applicable reliability standards and requirements), unless otherwise required pursuant to the SPP market rules and administration by SPP of those rules, including with respect to curtailment and dispatch priority, the Parties agree that they shall cause the High Majestic I and High Majestic II Projects to be curtailed as follows: (i) to the extent an Xcel or SPP system emergency has occurred and Xcel or SPP has specifically identified such system emergency as arising solely as a result of the High Majestic I Project, to the High Majestic I Project; (ii) second in all other circumstances in which a curtailment occurs under the LGIA (or pursuant to applicable operating guides or applicable reliability standards and requirements), to the High Majestic II Project; and (iii) third and last, to the High Majestic I Project. Notices: High Majestic Interconnection covenants and agrees to deliver to High Majestic I: Within 5 days after any officer or director of High Majestic Interconnection knows or has a reasonable basis to believe that any default under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements has occurred, a written notice of such event describing the same in detail reasonably satisfactory to High Majestic I and, together with such notice, a description of what action High Majestic Interconnection has taken and proposes to take with respect thereto. As soon as available and in any event within 25 days after the end date of each quarterly period occurring after the date hereof (commencing with the quarterly period ending March 31, 2012), a report with respect to each of the Projects for such quarterly period, which report shall set out any curtailments pursuant to any of the HMI and HMII Agreements affecting energy output and the reasons for such curtailments. Within 5 days after delivery or receipt thereof, a copy of each material notice, demand or other written communication in respect of any rights or obligations of any of High Majestic Interconnection, High Majestic I, High Majestic II, SPP and Xcel (collectively, the “Majestic Shared Facilities Parties”) given or received by any Majestic Shared Facilities Party pursuant to or relating to any of the HMI and HMII Agreements (including all written requests for amendments or waivers) or pursuant to or relating to any all governmental approvals necessary in connection with (i) the due execution and delivery of, and performance by each of the Parties and High Majestic II of its obligations and the exercise of its rights under each of the HMI and HMII Agreements to which they are party and (ii) the legality, validity and binding effect or enforceability of the HMI and HMII Agreements (the “Necessary Governmental Approvals”). Promptly, but in any event no later than five Business Days after any officer or director of High Majestic Interconnection obtains knowledge thereof: notice of any material litigation or governmental proceeding affecting High Majestic Interconnection; notice of any event constituting a force majeure under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements has occurred and is continuing; and notice of the termination, rescission or discharge (other than in accordance with its terms) of any provision of any of the HMI and HMII Agreements. Other Covenants: High Majestic Interconnection covenants and agrees: High Majestic Interconnection shall (i) preserve and maintain its legal existence as a limited liability company in good standing in each jurisdiction in which it owns or leases property or in which the conduct of its business requires it to so qualify, as applicable, and all of its material licenses, rights, privileges and franchises necessary for the maintenance of its corporate existence, and comply, in all material respects, with its formation and governance documents and (ii) not cancel, terminate, permit the cancellation or termination of, amend, modify or change any material terms or conditions of, or grant any material consent, waiver or approval under, or take or fail to take any other action that would impair the value of its interest or impair its rights under, any of its formation and governance documents. High Majestic Interconnection shall (i) obtain and maintain, and comply in all material respects with, all Necessary Governmental Approvals as shall now or hereafter be required under applicable laws and (ii) contest any proceeding which seeks or may reasonably be expected, to rescind, terminate, modify or suspend any Necessary Governmental Approval, unless such proceeding could not be reasonably be expected to materially adversely affect High Majestic Interconnection’s ability to carry out its obligations under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements. High Majestic Interconnection shall not create, incur, assume or suffer to exist any Lien upon any of its property, whether now owned or hereafter acquired, except Liens for taxes which are either not yet due, are subject to a Good Faith Contest, or otherwise bonds or reserves in an amount sufficient to repay the underlying obligation of such Lien shall have been established and remain in effect or except for such Liens that cannot be expected to materially adversely affect High Majestic Interconnection’s ability to carry out its obligations under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements (for purposes of this Agreement, “Lien” means, with respect to any property of any person, any mortgage, lien, deed of trust, hypothecation, fiduciary transfer of title, assignment by way of security, lien, pledge, charge, lease, sale and lease-back arrangement, easement, servitude, trust arrangement, or security interest or encumbrance of any kind in respect of such property, or any preferential arrangement having the practical effect of constituting a security interest with respect to the payment of any obligation with, or from the proceeds of, any property of any kind (and a person shall be deemed to own subject to a Lien any property that it has acquired or holds subject to the interest of a vendor or lessor under any conditional sale agreement, capital lease or other title retention agreement relating to such property). High Majestic Interconnection shall perform its obligations under the HMI and HMII Agreements in accordance with prudent industry practices. High Majestic Interconnection shall at all times (a) perform and observe all of its covenants and agreements contained in any of the HMI and HMII Agreements and (b) promptly take any and all action as may be reasonably necessary to enforce and preserve its material rights and to collect any and all sums due to it under the HMI and HMII Agreements, unless, in any such case, such enforcement shall not be in the commercially reasonable interest of any of the Majestic Shared Facilities Parties. High Majestic Interconnections shall not (i) merge or wind-up into or consolidate with any other person, or liquidate or dissolve itself (or suffer any liquidation or dissolution) or (ii) sell, lease, transfer, or otherwise dispose of its property other than ancillary services in connection with the HMI and HMII Agreements. High Majestic Interconnection shall not, except with the prior written approval of High Majestic I, (i) amend or modify, or consent to the amendment or modification of, any of the HMI and HMII Agreements or waive any material provision thereof, (ii) terminate, replace or assign any or all of its interests in any of the HMI and HMII Agreements or (iii) exercise any rights it may have to consent to any termination, replacement or assignment of any of the HMI and HMII Agreements by any party thereto or give any other material consent or exercise any material option thereunder; provided, however, that High Majestic Interconnection shall not be required to obtain the prior written approval of High Majestic I if any action described in clauses (i) through (iii) could not reasonably be expected to cause a material adverse effect on the High Majestic I Project or on High Majestic Interconnection’s ability to carry out its obligations under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements.
MATERIAL BREACH Material Breach by Either Party: In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party’s failure to cure such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from any other Party describing such breach, such non-breaching Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to (i) cure the breach on behalf of the breaching Party, or (ii) terminate this Agreement; provided, however, that in the event of any breach by a Party of this Agreement that may give rise to a breach by any other Party pursuant to the terms of the LGIA, such non-breaching Party shall not be required to provide the breaching Party hereunder with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to exercise the remedy specified in clause (i) of this sentence only; and provided, further, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender of such non-breaching Party. If a non-breaching Party (or any lender thereof) chooses to cure a breaching Party’s default, the breaching Party shall reimburse such non-breaching Party (or such Party’s lender) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by such non-breaching Party (or such non-breaching Party’s lender) in curing such breach. FORCE MAJEURE Force Majeure: In the event of an act of God, government order or restraint, war (declared or undeclared) or warlike conditions, act of terrorism, blockade, revolution, strike, lockout, civil commotion, fire, flood, storm, epidemic or any other occurrence beyond a Party’s reasonable control (each a “Force Majeure Event”), such Party shall promptly notify the other Party thereof and, so long as such condition shall persist, such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. The claiming Party shall give the other Party notice describing the particulars of the Force Majeure Event. Within fifteen (15) days after giving notice of the Force Majeure Event, the claiming Party shall give the other Party an estimate of the Force Majeure Event’s expected duration and probable impact. The claiming Party shall continue to furnish the other Party with timely regular reports during the continuation of the Force Majeure Event. Each Party shall immediately exercise commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit the impact to its obligations hereunder as a result of the Force Majeure Event. MISCELLANEOUS Effectiveness. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, this Agreement shall only be effective on the date upon which the assignment of the LGIA pursuant to the Assignment and Assumption Agreement, dated as of the date hereof, between High Majestic I and High Majestic Interconnection becomes effective in accordance with the terms thereof. Relationship of Parties: The Parties do not intend to create hereby any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business. Nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party. Non-Interference: Subject to Sections 2.2 and 2.3, each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the Common Facilities by any other Party as permitted hereunder. Modification and Amendment: The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all of the Parties. Waiver: The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party’s right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect. Enforceability: Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of the remaining provisions hereof. Assignment: No Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party without the prior written consent of each other Party, provided, however, that any Party may (a) collaterally assign this Agreement to any entity, or such entity’s agent, in connection with a financing or a refinancing of its respective Project or (b) assign this Agreement to any entity in connection with a foreclosure by any entity, or such entity’s agent, in connection with its collateral interest in this Agreement. Indemnification: Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold each other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death of any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party’s performance or non-performance of its obligations under this Agreement, except in cases of gross negligence or intentional wrongdoing, by the indemnified party. However, in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any losses, damages, costs or expenses for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability; provided, however, that damages for which a Party may be liable to any other Party under another agreement will not be considered to be special, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages hereunder. Governing Law: This Agreement shall be governed by and constructed in accordance with the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to its conflict of laws provisions. Inspection of Records: Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Common Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times. Entire Agreement: This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof. Section Headings: The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. Counterparts: This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument. Specific Performance: The Parties hereto may demand specific performance of this Agreement. Each Party hereby irrevocably waives any defense based on the adequacy of a remedy at law and any other defense which might be asserted to bar the remedy of specific performance. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, High Majestic II agrees to: Operate the High Majestic II Project in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the LGIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the LGIA; Facilitate High Majestic Interconnection’s compliance with all provisions of the LGIA to which High Majestic Interconnection is subject (and all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as it relates to the High Majestic II Project; Not take any action (nor refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the LGIA by High Majestic Interconnection; Use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of its Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default under the LGIA, and if such default occurs, to promptly assist High Majestic Interconnection to cure such default in accordance with the terms of the LGIA; Comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by High Majestic Interconnection, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the LGIA with respect to the High Majestic II Project; Provide High Majestic Interconnection with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of the High Majestic II Project required for High Majestic Interconnection to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the LGIA; and Provide to High Majestic Interconnection copies of all notices and instructions received by it that affect High Majestic Interconnection’s performance under the LGIA. Prior Written Consent: Except as set forth in this Agreement, neither Party shall take any action that results in the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights or increases the obligations or responsibilities of the other Party under this Agreement, without the prior written consent of the other Party. No Joint and Several Liability with High Majestic I: The Parties acknowledge that this Agreement does not subject High Majestic II to joint and several liability for any actions taken by High Majestic I that may cause non-compliance by High Majestic Interconnection with the LGIA. COST REIMBURSEMENT Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses: Under the LGIA, High Majestic Interconnection is responsible for certain expenses, including potential costs under Section 10.5 of the LGIA for operations and maintenance expenses. Such expenses, and those expenses incurred to administer Coordination Services to High Majestic I and High Majestic II which are not directly caused by either High Majestic I or High Majestic II, shall be paid for as provided in Section 9 of the Common Facilities Agreement, CHANGE IN LAW Change in Law: In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Coordination Service or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement. CERTAIN COVENANTS Authority and Operational Abilities: Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement. Adverse Events: If an operational issue arises at the High Majestic I Project or High Majestic II Project that is reasonably expected to result in a breach by High Majestic Interconnection of the LGIA or this Agreement (an “Adverse Event”), High Majestic Interconnection shall promptly take all commercially reasonable action to resolve such issue, including curtailing the Project that is causing the Adverse Event. In the event of such curtailment, energy deliveries to the to the Point of Interconnection (as defined in the LGIA) from the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall be limited as necessary until the Adverse Event has been cured. If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event caused by the High Majestic I Project or the High Majestic II Project, High Majestic Interconnection incurs costs, expenses, or penalties of any kind, the Project that has caused such Adverse Event shall be solely responsible for reimbursing High Majestic Interconnection for any such costs, expenses or penalties. In the event that both Projects are responsible for the Adverse Event, and to the extent that High Majestic Interconnection, in its reasonable discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Adverse Event between the Projects, each Project shall be responsible for its allocable portion of the applicable costs, expenses or penalties. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for High Majestic Interconnection, as determined in its reasonable discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, each Project will be liable for its Pro Rata Share (as defined in the Common Facilities Agreement) of such costs, expenses or penalties. Priority of Curtailment: Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, in the event of curtailment pursuant to the LGIA (or pursuant to applicable operating guides or applicable reliability standards and requirements), unless otherwise required pursuant to the SPP market rules and administration by SPP of those rules, including with respect to curtailment and dispatch priority, the Parties agree that they shall cause the High Majestic I and High Majestic II Projects to be curtailed as follows: (i) to the extent an Xcel or SPP system emergency has occurred and Xcel or SPP has specifically identified such system emergency as arising solely as a result of the High Majestic I Project, to the High Majestic I Project; (ii) second in all other circumstances in which a curtailment occurs under the LGIA (or pursuant to applicable operating guides or applicable reliability standards and requirements), to the High Majestic II Project; and (iii) third and last, to the High Majestic I Project. Notices: High Majestic Interconnection covenants and agrees to deliver to High Majestic II: Within 5 days after any officer or director of High Majestic Interconnection knows or has a reasonable basis to believe that any default under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements has occurred, a written notice of such event describing the same in detail reasonably satisfactory to High Majestic II and, together with such notice, a description of what action High Majestic Interconnection has taken and proposes to take with respect thereto. Within 5 days after delivery or receipt thereof, a copy of each material notice, demand or other written communication in respect of any rights or obligations of any of High Majestic Interconnection, High Majestic I, High Majestic II, SPP and Xcel (collectively, the “Majestic Shared Facilities Parties”) given or received by any Majestic Shared Facilities Party pursuant to or relating to any of the HMI and HMII Agreements (including all written requests for amendments or waivers) or pursuant to or relating to any all governmental approvals necessary in connection with (i) the due execution and delivery of, and performance by each of the Parties and High Majestic I of its obligations and the exercise of its rights under each of the HMI and HMII Agreements to which they are party and (ii) the legality, validity and binding effect or enforceability of the HMI and HMII Agreements (the “Necessary Governmental Approvals”). Promptly, but in any event no later than five Business Days after any officer or director of High Majestic Interconnection obtains knowledge thereof: notice of any material litigation or governmental proceeding affecting High Majestic Interconnection; notice of any event constituting a force majeure under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements has occurred and is continuing; and notice of the termination, rescission or discharge (other than in accordance with its terms) of any provision of any of the HMI and HMII Agreements. Other Covenants: High Majestic Interconnection covenants and agrees: High Majestic Interconnection shall (i) preserve and maintain its legal existence as a limited liability company in good standing in each jurisdiction in which it owns or leases property or in which the conduct of its business requires it to so qualify, as applicable, and all of its material licenses, rights, privileges and franchises necessary for the maintenance of its corporate existence, and comply, in all material respects, with its formation and governance documents and (ii) not cancel, terminate, permit the cancellation or termination of, amend, modify or change any material terms or conditions of, or grant any material consent, waiver or approval under, or take or fail to take any other action that would impair the value of its interest or impair its rights under, any of its formation and governance documents. High Majestic Interconnection shall (i) obtain and maintain, and comply in all material respects with, all Necessary Governmental Approvals as shall now or hereafter be required under applicable laws and (ii) contest any proceeding which seeks or may reasonably be expected, to rescind, terminate, modify or suspend any Necessary Governmental Approval, unless such proceeding could not be reasonably be expected to materially adversely affect High Majestic Interconnection’s ability to carry out its obligations under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements. High Majestic Interconnection shall not create, incur, assume or suffer to exist any Lien upon any of its property, whether now owned or hereafter acquired, except Liens for taxes which are either not yet due, are subject to a Good Faith Contest, or otherwise bonds or reserves in an amount sufficient to repay the underlying obligation of such Lien shall have been established and remain in effect or except for such Liens that cannot be expected to materially adversely affect High Majestic Interconnection’s ability to carry out its obligations under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements (for purposes of this Agreement, “Lien” means, with respect to any property of any person, any mortgage, lien, deed of trust, hypothecation, fiduciary transfer of title, assignment by way of security, lien, pledge, charge, lease, sale and lease-back arrangement, easement, servitude, trust arrangement, or security interest or encumbrance of any kind in respect of such property, or any preferential arrangement having the practical effect of constituting a security interest with respect to the payment of any obligation with, or from the proceeds of, any property of any kind (and a person shall be deemed to own subject to a Lien any property that it has acquired or holds subject to the interest of a vendor or lessor under any conditional sale agreement, capital lease or other title retention agreement relating to such property)). High Majestic Interconnection shall perform its obligations under the HMI and HMII Agreements in accordance with prudent industry practices. High Majestic Interconnection shall at all times (a) perform and observe all of its covenants and agreements contained in any of the HMI and HMII Agreements and (b) promptly take any and all action as may be reasonably necessary to enforce and preserve its material rights and to collect any and all sums due to it under the HMI and HMII Agreements, unless, in any such case, such enforcement shall not be in the commercially reasonable interest of any of the Majestic Shared Facilities Parties. High Majestic Interconnections shall not (i) merge or wind-up into or consolidate with any other person, or liquidate or dissolve itself (or suffer any liquidation or dissolution) or (ii) sell, lease, transfer, or otherwise dispose of its property other than ancillary services in connection with the HMI and HMII Agreements. High Majestic Interconnection shall not, except with the prior written approval of High Majestic II, (i) amend or modify, or consent to the amendment or modification of, any of the HMI and HMII Agreements or waive any material provision thereof, (ii) terminate, replace or assign any or all of its interests in any of the HMI and HMII Agreements or (iii) exercise any rights it may have to consent to any termination, replacement or assignment of any of the HMI and HMII Agreements by any party thereto or give any other material consent or exercise any material option thereunder; provided, however, that High Majestic Interconnection shall not be required to obtain the prior written approval of High Majestic II if any action described in clauses (i) through (iii) could not reasonably be expected to cause a material adverse effect on the High Majestic II Project or on High Majestic Interconnection’s ability to carry out its obligations under any of the HMI and HMII Agreements.
MATERIAL BREACH Material Breach by Either Party: In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party’s failure to cure such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from any other Party describing such breach, such non-breaching Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to (i) cure the breach on behalf of the breaching Party, or (ii) terminate this Agreement; provided, however, that in the event of any breach by a Party of this Agreement that may give rise to a breach by any other Party pursuant to the terms of the LGIA, such non-breaching Party shall not be required to provide the breaching Party hereunder with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to exercise the remedy specified in clause (i) of this sentence only; and provided, further, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender of such non-breaching Party. If a non-breaching Party (or any lender thereof) chooses to cure a breaching Party’s default, the breaching Party shall reimburse such non-breaching Party (or such Party’s lender) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by such non-breaching Party (or such non-breaching Party’s lender) in curing such breach. FORCE MAJEURE Force Majeure: In the event of an act of God, government order or restraint, war (declared or undeclared) or warlike conditions, act of terrorism, blockade, revolution, strike, lockout, civil commotion, fire, flood, storm, epidemic or any other occurrence beyond a Party’s reasonable control (each a “Force Majeure Event”), such Party shall promptly notify the other Party thereof and, so long as such condition shall persist, such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. The claiming Party shall give the other Party notice describing the particulars of the Force Majeure Event. Within fifteen (15) days after giving notice of the Force Majeure Event, the claiming Party shall give the other Party an estimate of the Force Majeure Event’s expected duration and probable impact. The claiming Party shall continue to furnish the other Party with timely regular reports during the continuation of the Force Majeure Event. Each Party shall immediately exercise commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit the impact to its obligations hereunder as a result of the Force Majeure Event. MISCELLANEOUS Effectiveness. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, this Agreement shall only be effective on the date upon which the assignment of the LGIA pursuant to the Assignment and Assumption Agreement, dated as of the date hereof, between High Majestic I and High Majestic Interconnection becomes effective in accordance with the terms thereof. Relationship of Parties: The Parties do not intend to create hereby any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business. Nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party. Non-Interference: Subject to Sections 2.2 and 2.3, each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the Common Facilities by any other Party as permitted hereunder. Modification and Amendment: The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all of the Parties. Waiver: The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party’s right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect. Enforceability: Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of the remaining provisions hereof. Assignment: No Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party without the prior written consent of each other Party, provided, however, that any Party may (a) collaterally assign this Agreement to any entity, or such entity’s agent, in connection with a financing or a refinancing of its respective Project or (b) assign this Agreement to any entity in connection with a foreclosure by any entity, or such entity’s agent, in connection with its collateral interest in this Agreement. Indemnification: Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold each other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death of any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party’s performance or non-performance of its obligations under this Agreement, except in cases of gross negligence or intentional wrongdoing, by the indemnified party. However, in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any losses, damages, costs or expenses for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability; provided, however, that damages for which a Party may be liable to any other Party under another agreement will not be considered to be special, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages hereunder. Governing Law: This Agreement shall be governed by and constructed in accordance with the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to its conflict of laws provisions. Inspection of Records: Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Common Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times. Entire Agreement: This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof. Section Headings: The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. Counterparts: This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument. Specific Performance: The Parties hereto may demand specific performance of this Agreement. Each Party hereby irrevocably waives any defense based on the adequacy of a remedy at law and any other defense which might be asserted to bar the remedy of specific performance.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Coordination Services Agreement to be executed as of the date first written above.
